coachella day 1 🖤🩸
better 3 weeks late than never?? finally getting around to posting these! so many good mems 🥹 swipe to see my boyfriend being a little *too* committed to his task of getting candid content (aka just starting to film immediately after me asking lol)

day 2 🤘🏻⚡️🎸

day 3 🎡🪩

I had the absolutely incredible experience of going to Sedona, AZ w/ my business coach & friend @elisaowencoaching 🏜️ it was a VIP experience that was a bonus she was running at the end of last year & so she planned a weekend full of surprises for us 🌵🦋🫶🏻
1. we attended an AMAZING @clothandflame celestial themed dinner. every person from the staff to the attendees were so lovely & great to talk to
2. I loveee sitting on the ground & I'm so glad I found someone who is just as comfy on the ground in the middle of a fancy dinner setting as I am LOL 🫶🏻
3. it’s gotten hot in phoenix so I was excited to escape up north... I definitely didn't expect the weather to be so chilly/windy & wasn't very prepared lol thankfully the dinner got moved inside or else I think I would have froze ❄️
4. since the dinner was star themed there were tons of telescopes to look through, including this one that was handmade by the astronomer 🔭
5. I thrifted the leather jacket of my dreams recently & I cleaned it, however, I apparently didn't open the pockets at all? (whoops , pretty gross 🥲) but this led to the amazing surprise haul of a purple hair tie, used chapstick, receipt from 2009 & $14 which officially paid for the jacket lol 🤩🧡
6. earlier on the 1st day we went for an aura picture/psychic reading. my aura is orange (creative, action-oriented & positive) w/ green on the outside (love for yourself/others, compassionate, empathetic) which is very fitting for me 🎨 when we did a tarot reading I drew the caterpillar card 🐛 I've been in a transformative part of my life & had been comparing it to a caterpillar going into a cocoon so this was kismet 🦋
7. got to enjoy this band that had people playing tons of fun things like a washtub bass, the spoons & a washboard 
8. the next day we went on a guided hike where we learned about vortexes, some of Sedona's history including it's significance to many different Indigenous tribes, & we did some breath work 🏜️
9. no matter how many times I visit, Sedona's beauty continues to take my breath away! 
10. if you made it all the way to the end enjoy this pic that made me realize just how bony my spine is hahaha stegosaurus vibes 🦕

the growthhhhhh 🥹🎨🤍
making these type of videos always makes me emotional!! it’s so cool to see how much I’ve grown over the last 4 years ♡  it’s hard when you’re in the midst of everything to really clearly see your whole journey. I often feel like I “should be further” in my skills, like I should have more techniques *perfected* or should be quicker at applying the looks but reflecting back on how much I’ve grown and how much more I can accomplish in similar amounts of time I’m incredibly proud of myself! remember that we’re all always learning, growing, and progressing whether or not it feels like it in the moment 🫶🏻

yellowstone has my heart 💛🌲⛺️
I haven’t been since I was really little & don’t remember much so I definitely felt like a first timer! it was more beautiful than I could ever put into words and I already want to go back 🫶🏻 
1. I always feel most at home among the pine trees
2. if you had me describe the most beautiful place, it would be this 🥹
3. the hot springs are INCREDIBLY gorgeous but also INCREDIBLY stinky lol
4. most people think that yellowstone is primarily in montana but pretty much all of it is in wyoming
5. my grandma was a wildlife biologist & worked at yellowstone for a summer so it was cool hearing all her old stories 🫶🏻
6. we went through cody, wy & had to visit buffalo bill’s iconic irma hotel (it opened in 1902 😵)
7. we obviously had to stop in jackson hole on our drive & I can never get over these archways made completely out of antlers 🦌 
8. we visited grand teton national park too & stayed in these gorgeous historic log cabins at colter bay village 
9. my toxic trait is looking at any “crafty” project & thinking I could definitely master it 😅 after staying in these cabins I’m convinced I could pretty easily make a wooden cabin
10. I don’t think I’ll ever grow up & I’m 100% ok with that 🥰
